President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the Commonwealth of Massachusetts, providing federal assistance for recovery efforts following a severe winter storm and flooding in March 2018. The federal funding will support emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. James N. Russo has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.